"title": "8744: faithlessness, as disobedience",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8744: faithlessness, as disobedience",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A lack of faith and obedience to God, which is seen especially in the lives of unbelievers. However, Scripture makes clear that believers can occasionally lapse into faithlessness towards God.</p>\n<h2>Faithlessness among the ungodly</h2>\n<h3>In their character and lifestyle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:3-Ps101:5\">PSA 101:3–101:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:158\">PSA 119:158</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:4\">PSA 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:1\">PSA 14:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:8-John16:9\">JHN 16:8–16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:2\">2TH 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:15-Titus1:16\">TIT 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of faithless men</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:2-1Sam25:3\">1SA 25:2–25:3</a> <em>Nabal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:5-Esth3:6\">EST 3:5–3:6</a> <em>Haman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:16\">MAT 2:16</a> <em>Herod the Great</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:23-Acts19:27\">ACT 19:23–19:27</a> <em>Demetrius</em></p>\n<h3>The faithless appear to prosper</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:1\">JER 12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:7\">JOB 21:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:3-Ps73:5\">PSA 73:3–73:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:12\">PSA 73:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:15\">MAL 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Faithlessness results in judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:14\">PRO 14:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:36\">JHN 3:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:17-Ps73:18\">PSA 73:17–73:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:27\">PSA 73:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:1\">MAL 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:16\">MRK 16:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:24\">JHN 8:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:12\">2TH 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></p>\n<h2>Faithlessness among the Jews</h2>\n<h3>Their failure to trust God for deliverance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:8-Isa22:11\">ISA 22:8–22:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:12-Isa30:13\">ISA 30:12–30:13</a></p>\n<h3>Their rejection of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:37-John12:38\">JHN 12:37–12:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:1\">ISA 53:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:11-John3:12\">JHN 3:11–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:37-John5:40\">JHN 5:37–5:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:45\">JHN 8:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:25-John10:26\">JHN 10:25–10:26</a></p>\n<h3>Specific examples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:58\">MAT 13:58</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:5-Mark6:6\">MRK 6:5–6:6</a> <em>the people of Nazareth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21-Matt19:22\">MAT 19:21–19:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21-Mark10:22\">MRK 10:21–10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22-Luke18:23\">LUK 18:22–18:23</a> <em>the rich young ruler</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:24\">ACT 28:24</a> <em>Many Jews reject Paul's ministry in Rome</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:13\">1TI 1:13</a> <em>Paul's own persecution of the church arose from unbelief in Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h3>Israel's estrangement from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:43\">MAT 21:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:22\">PSA 118:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:41\">MAT 21:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:9\">MRK 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:32-Rom9:33\">ROM 9:32–9:33</a></p>\n<h3>The acceptance of the Gentiles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:17-Rom11:21\">ROM 11:17–11:21</a> <em>The Jews' rejection of the gospel opens the way for Gentiles to be incorporated into the people of God, represented here as branches grafted onto a cultivated olive tree.</em></p>\n<h3>Israel's faithlessness is partial and temporary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:5\">ROM 11:5</a> <em>Though the people as a whole have rejected Jesus Christ, a faithful remnant remains</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:11-Rom11:12\">ROM 11:11–11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:23-Rom11:27\">ROM 11:23–11:27</a> <em>God's purpose for the faithful of Israel is their ultimate salvation.</em></p>\n<h2>Faithlessness among believers</h2>\n<h3>Lack of faith is rebuked</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:30-Matt14:31\">MAT 14:30–14:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:30-Matt6:32\">MAT 6:30–6:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:28-Luke12:30\">LUK 12:28–12:30</a> <em>worrying about food and clothing</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:24-Matt8:26\">MAT 8:24–8:26</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:38-Mark4:40\">MRK 4:38–4:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:23-Luke8:25\">LUK 8:23–8:25</a> <em>Fear during a storm at sea</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:17-Matt17:20\">MAT 17:17–17:20</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17-Mark9:19\">MRK 9:17–9:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:40-Luke9:42\">LUK 9:40–9:42</a> <em>inability to cast out a demon</em></p>\n<h3>Causes of faithlessness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:8-Matt16:10\">MAT 16:8–16:10</a> <em>failure to learn from the lessons of the past</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:25\">LUK 24:25</a> <em>failure to accept teaching that has been given</em></p>",
